Australia’s Southern Seawater Desalination Plant to Double Capacity

-- B y   J a s o n   S c o t t
-- 
2011-08-01T06:06:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/australia-s-southern-seawater-desalination-plant-to-double-capacity.html
Capacity at  Western Australia ’s
Southern Seawater Desalination Plant will be doubled to provide
100 billion liters of drinking water a year, the state
government said in an e-mailed statement today. The first stage
of the plant in the state’s south-west was been built during the
past two and half years at a cost of A$955 million, it said.
Work on the $450 million expansion will start immediately.  To contact the reporter on this story:
